The paper deals with fast nearest neighbor search for the Wasserstein distance, which is a similarity measure commonly used in image and text domains. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Among these, cs.DS is the most likely category since the paper focuses on developing tree-based approximation algorithms for nearest neighbor search. The other categories are also relevant since the paper deals with image and text datasets and involves machine learning and information theory concepts.
